  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nBamboo\nObject Info\n45 sec\n40\nSource\n( ×3)\nDropped by\n()\nMiscellaneous\n\"bamboo\"\n“Maybe I can bamboozle my enemies with this?”\n–Wilson\n“Looks flammable.”\n–Willow\n“Very mighty building material!”\n–Wolfgang\n“Green sticks... who cares...”\n–Wendy\n“IT'S A VERSATILE ENGINEERING MATERIAL”\n–WX-78\n“A useful material of high tensile strength.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“It's like diet wood, eh?”\n–Woodie\n“I have several ideas in mind for this.”\n–Maxwell\n“A versatile and pliable perennial plant I can use to make stuff.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Sticks öf great versatility.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Such a useful stick-type thing.”\n–Webber\n“This looks pretty float-atious.”\n–Walani\n“Bamboo shoots are excellent on a nice bed of rice.”\n–Warly\n“Ye'd be too big ta pick me teeth wit'. If me had teeth...”\n–Woodlegs\n“IS'T TREE STUFFS O' BENDINESS”\n–Wilba\n“Greenstick”\n–Wormwood\n“One piece is nice. Many pieces are nicer.”\n–Wheeler\nBamboo is a renewable resource that can be gathered by hacking down a Bamboo Patch with a Machete in the Shipwrecked DLC. It can also be obtained by hammering a Wildbore House or a Wildbore Head.\nIt is used in many Nautical recipes and can also be refined into Cloth.\nHamlet[edit | edit source]\nBamboo is also included in the Hamlet DLC where it can be bought for 3 Oincs at 'The Sty' Oddities Emporium in the Pig City. There is also a small chance(around 7%) for Bamboo to be obtained from hammering the 'A Smashing Pot. Using a Shears on a Bamboo Patch will result in 2 Bamboo instead of the usual one.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×3\n×4\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×3\n×8\n×5\n×4\n×5\n×2\n×4\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nIt was originally assumed that Bamboo was a Wood Food Type and could also be eaten by Werebeaver and would give 10 Beaverness\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items",
